Christian,

You need to compile Cantera with the same version of gcc that MATLAB 
itself was compiled with.  On the MathWorks web site they have 
information about the compiler versions for various operating systems.

The problem may be related to changes in libstdc++ in gcc 4.x compared 
to gcc 3.x. As I understand it, libstdc++ in gcc 4 is a shared library, 
while in gcc 3 it was a static library. There are probably other 
incompatibilities between the two versions.

Some linux systems maintain more than one version of the gcc compilers. 
  You may be able to specify which one to use in the Cantera &#39;configure&#39; 
script, to match the one required by MATLAB.

I&#39;m sorry I can&#39;t be of more help, but currently I do not have access 
to a linux machine that has MATLAB installed, so I can&#39;t diagnose the 
problem myself.  Has anyone else encountered and solved this problem?


Dave


